'''''Psychology of Religion and Spirituality''''' is an [[peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] in [[psychology]] published by the [[American Psychological Association]]. It publishes original articles that deal with the psychology of [[religion]] and [[spirituality]]. Methods covered include critical reviews as well as experimental, correlational, and qualitative approaches. Topics of interest include training and practice.

The journal was established in 2009 and is abstracted and indexed by [[Scopus]],<ref name=scopuslink>[http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/journal/19411022 Sciverse/Scopus listing of ''Psychology of Religion and Spirituality''] (accessed 18 Oct 2011</ref> [[PsycINFO]], [[Arts & Humanities Citation Index]], [[ATLA Religion Database|ATLA]], [[Current Contents]], [[Journal Citation Reports|Journal Citation Reports / Social Sciences Edition]], and [[Social Sciences Citation Index]].<ref>[http://www.apa.org/pubs/journals/rel/index.aspx journal information page (abstracting and indexing tab)] (accessed 18 Oct 2011)</ref><ref name=APAcat>[http://www.apa.org/pubs/journals/catalog.pdf Journals Program of the American Psychological Association] (accessed 18 October 2011): Page 37 lists the journal as accessed in ATLA, Journal Citation Reports / Social Sciences Edition, PsycINFO, SCOPUS, and Social Sciences Citation index.</ref>

